The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sehwag decision today

New Delhi: Opening batsman Virender Sehwags availability for the first one-day International against England would only be known after he undergoes a fitness test here on Sunday. 

Sehwag, who suffered a back spasms during the third and final Test in Mumbai this week, would be assessed of his condition during the Team Indias practice session, on Sunday, at the Kotla. 

The first ODI will be played at the Kotla on Tuesday. 

Sehwags inclusion will be dependent upon participating and passing a full net session tomorrow with the squad, BCCI secretary Niranjan Shah said on Saturday. 

Sehwag has improved significantly with respect to his back injury. 

He is confident of being available for the first ODI. His clinical signs are presently very promising. 

Sehwag, underwent a medical assessment by physio John Gloster, who has already arrived in the city, on Saturday. 

Besides Sehwag, his Gautam Gambhir is the only other regular opener in the 15-member squad for the first three ODIs. 

Chairman of selectors Kiran More said any decision on replacement would be made only after a report on Sehwag is made available. 

We have named him in the team. We expect him to be fit. Let us wait till tomorrow, said More. 

Meanwhile, Shah also said that Anil Kumbles left knee has improved. (PTI) 




